'''Ilana Dayan-Orbach''' ({{lang-he|<U+05D0><U+05D9><U+05DC><U+05E0><U+05D4> <U+05D3><U+05D9><U+05D9><U+05DF>}}, born 1964) is an [[Israel]]i investigative journalist, jurist and anchorwoman. She is best known as host of the investigative television program ''Uvda'' ("Fact") on the [[Channel 2 (Israel)|Israeli Channel 2]].

==Biography==
Dayan was born in [[Argentina]] in 1964 and [[Aliyah|immigrated]] to Israel with her family in 1970, and settled in the [[Yad Eliyahu]] neighborhood in [[Tel Aviv]].<ref name=keshet>{{Cite web
| title = <U+05E2><U+05D5><U+05D1><U+05D3><U+05D4>
| work = Keshet-TV
| accessdate = 2008-03-14
| url = http://www.keshet-tv.com/UvdaReporter.aspx?ID=61248
}} {{he icon}}</ref> Her grandfather's father, Eliyahu Dayan (1868-1925) was [[Shmuel Dayan]]'s uncle.

She was drafted to the [[Israel Defense Forces|IDF]] during the [[First Lebanon War]] and served as producer, editor and correspondent for the [[Israel Army Radio]]. She was the first woman correspondent in the station's history. Near the end of her regular service she began presenting the morning program with [[Yitzhak Ben-Ner]], and later with [[Micha Friedman]]. At the age of 23 became the first woman on the presenting staff of ''Erev Hadash'' ("New Evening") on the [[Israeli Educational Television]].<ref name=keshet/>

Meanwhile, she attended the [[Tel Aviv University]] school of law, and after her internship she traveled to the [[United States]] to receive a PhD in law from the [[Yale University]]. During her studies there, she also wrote a bi-weekly column for [[Yediot Aharonot]]. On her return to Israel she began teaching courses in [[constitutional law]] in the Tel Aviv University faculty of law, where she still teaches as a visiting lecturer.<ref name=keshet/> She has expressed her support for [[Supreme Court of Israel]] President [[Dorit Beinisch]] and denounced [[Minister of Justice of Israel|Justice Minister]] [[Daniel Friedmann]]'s attempts to limit the supreme court's [[judicial review]].<ref name=asheri>{{Cite news
| last = Asheri
| first = Ehud
| title = Behind the Lines / Wholly Mozes
| work = Haaretz
| accessdate = 2008-03-14
| date = 2007-11-29
| url = http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/spages/927198.html
}}</ref>

On November 1993, when the Israeli channel 2 was launched, she started hosting her television program, ''Uvda'' for [[Telad]]. It is the only program still being broadcasted on that channel for such a long time. In 2005, Uvda was purchased by [[Keshet (TV)|Keshet]], after Telad's concession was over. She also presents a morning program on current affairs for the Israel Army Radio.<ref name=keshet/>

She is married to Harel and is the mother of Yael, Zohar and Gonen.<ref name=keshet/> In 2005, she was voted 106 in [[Ynet]]'s list of [[200 Greatest Israelis]],<ref name=benyovitch>{{Cite news
| last = <U+05D1><U+05E0><U+05D9><U+05D5><U+05D1><U+05D9><U+05E5>'
| first = <U+05D2><U+05D9><U+05D0>
