==Controversies==
===The Captain R. affair===
{{see|Iman Darweesh Al Hams}}
In 2005 Uvda broadcast a documentary on the killing of 13 year old Iman Darweesh Al Hams by IDF troops in the [[Gaza Strip]]. According to her investigation, the commanding officer, identified as Captain R. verified her death by shooting her from point-blank range.<ref name=lynfield>{{Cite news
| last = Lynfield
| first = Ben
| title = Israeli army under fire after killing girl
| work = The Christian Science Monitor
| accessdate = 2008-03-14
| date = 2004-11-26
| url = http://www.csmonitor.com/2004/1126/p07s01-wome.html
}}</ref> Captain R. was eventually acquitted by a court martial. Following his Acquittal, he filed a lawsuit against her and channel 2 for libel.<ref name=carmel2>{{Cite news
| last = Carmel
| first = Asaf
| title = Journalist Ilana Dayan, Channel 2 submit defense in Cpt. R. libel suit
| work = Haaretz
| accessdate = 2008-03-14
| date = 2006-07-02
| url = http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/pages/ShArt.jhtml?itemNo=733743
}}</ref> The Jerusalem District Court has denied Captain R.'s demand that Dayan reveal her sources.<ref name=roth>{{Cite news
| last = <U+05E8><U+05D5><U+05D8>
| first = <U+05E0><U+05D5><U+05E8><U+05D9><U+05EA>
