===The Brothers Parinyan affair===
in April 2005 Uvda suggested that a senior police officer, Yoram Levy, a senior police officer, was effectively representing the interests of the Parinyan crime family within the police, after criminal Pinhas Buhbut was murdered by a cop. Following the program, a police investigation found Levy not guilty and close the case, but did write down a disciplinary offense for Levy for using the brothers as sources. Near the end of the year, the [[Zeiler Commission]] appointed to investigate the police proceedings during the affair. according to Justice Vardi Zeiler, "if not for Ilana Dayan and her television program, this case wouldn't have been revived and no one would have known what happened. These are things that can be said with absolute certainty".<ref name=shavit>{{Cite news
| last = Shavit
| first = Ari
| coauthors = Yuval Yoaz
| title = Zeiler: Israel could be on its way to becoming mafia-type regime
| work = Haaretz
| accessdate = 2008-03-14
| date = 2007-02-22
| url = http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/spages/828647.html
}}</ref> The commission report eventually led to the resignation of police commissioner [[Moshe Karadi]] and the discharge of Levy.<ref name=feldman>{{Cite news
| last = Feldman
| first = Avigdor
| title = Scripted by Scorsese?
| work = Haaretz
| accessdate = 2008-03-14
| url = http://news.haaretz.co.il/hasen/pages/ShArtStEngPE.jhtml?itemNo=829389&contrassID=2&subContrassID=15&title='Scripted%20by%20Scorsese?%20'&dyn_server=172.20.5.5
}}</ref> Levy filed a lawsuit for libel against Dayan,<ref name=hason>{{Cite news
| last = <U+05D7><U+05E1><U+05D5><U+05DF>
| first = <U+05E0><U+05D9><U+05E8>
| title = <U+05E0><U+05E6>"<U+05DE> <U+05D9><U+05D5><U+05E8><U+05DD> <U+05DC><U+05D5><U+05D9> <U+05D4><U+05D2><U+05D9><U+05E9> <U+05EA><U+05D1><U+05D9><U+05E2><U+05EA> <U+05D3><U+05D9><U+05D1><U+05D4> <U+05E0><U+05D2><U+05D3> <U+05D0><U+05D9><U+05DC><U+05E0><U+05D4> <U+05D3><U+05D9><U+05D9><U+05DF>
| work = Haaretz
| accessdate = 2008-03-15
| date = 2007-03-28
