===The Moshe Katsav affair===
{{see|Moshe Katsav#2006 rape and sexual harassment charges}}
In March 2007, ''Uvda'' was accused of portraying the suspended [[President of Israel]], [[Moshe Katsav]], as fraternizing with criminals and systematically sexually assaulting female employees and then intimidating them into silence on the eve of his hearing with Attorney General [[Menachem Mazuz]]<ref name="stoil">{{Cite news
| last = Stoil
| first = Rebecca Anna
| coauthors = Dan Izenberg
| title = Katsav suspected of additional rape
| work = Jerusalem Post
| accessdate = 2008-03-15
| date = 2007-03-29
| url = http://www.jpost.com/servlet/Satellite?pagename=JPost/JPArticle/ShowFull&cid=1173879202855
}}</ref> by Katsav's attorneys, who said they would file a slander suit against Dayan.<ref name=yoaz>{{Cite news
| last = Yoaz
| first = Yuval
| title = Katsav questioned for allegedly raping accuser more than once
| work = Haaretz
| accessdate = 2008-03-14
| date = 2007-03-29
| url = http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/spages/843726.html
}}</ref>

